Under the optimal conditions, a highly efficient and sensitive PEC aptasensor for OTC detection can be prepared as stated above. As shown in Fig. 5
                        A, as the OTC concentration increased, the photocurrent decreased gradually. And Fig. 5B showed the corresponding linear calibration curve which was the function of the photocurrent response with the OTC concentration, ranging from 0.1 nM to 150 nM. The detection limit was estimated to be 0.03 nM (S/N = 3), which was lower than previous methods for OTC detection (Table 1
                        ), therefore, this sensor has good analytical performance for OTC detection.
